The paper deals with a privacy-preserving algorithm for Group Testing, which involves information-theoretic principles and secrecy constraints. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
